Sentencas: Due to the mixed ionic electronic conductive properties of the Lanthanum Strontium Cobalt Ferrite (LSCF) La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta compound, it is of great scientific and technological interest.
Titulo: A 2D and 3D X-ray μ-diffraction and μ-fluorescence study of a mixed ionic electronic conductor

Sentencas: Especially in the Solid Oxide Fuel Cell (SOFC) technology, this compound has receiving great attention as a cathode material.
Titulo: A 2D and 3D X-ray μ-diffraction and μ-fluorescence study of a mixed ionic electronic conductor

Sentencas: However, its chemical reactivity with the Yttria-stabilized Zirconia (YSZ) electrolyte still remains one of the main challenges, which demands a comprehension in the gm and sub-gm range.
Titulo: A 2D and 3D X-ray μ-diffraction and μ-fluorescence study of a mixed ionic electronic conductor

Sentencas: In order to address the reactivity issues locally in the micrometre scale range, 2D and 3D X-ray mu-diffraction and mu-fluorescence analysis have been performed on a pristine LSCF cathode layer.
Titulo: A 2D and 3D X-ray μ-diffraction and μ-fluorescence study of a mixed ionic electronic conductor

Sentencas: The cathode was deposited on a dense YSZ electrolyte substrate spaced by a thin Gadolinium doped Ceria Oxide (CGO) barrier layer in between LSCF and YSZ to limit the reactivity.
Titulo: A 2D and 3D X-ray μ-diffraction and μ-fluorescence study of a mixed ionic electronic conductor

Sentencas: The present approach offers a larger field of view in comparison to electron microscopy techniques.
Titulo: A 2D and 3D X-ray μ-diffraction and μ-fluorescence study of a mixed ionic electronic conductor

Sentencas: The method can provide a more representative information and may offer some insights on the reactivity distribution along the interfaces.
Titulo: A 2D and 3D X-ray μ-diffraction and μ-fluorescence study of a mixed ionic electronic conductor

Sentencas: The formation of micro SrZrO3 inclusions in LSCF layer is then indubitably identified, as well as in the CGO/YSZ interface.
Titulo: A 2D and 3D X-ray μ-diffraction and μ-fluorescence study of a mixed ionic electronic conductor
